# Frontend / Backend Boundary Rules

Frontend must never implement security decisions.

Frontend may only use permission flags returned by the backend.

Examples:

canWrite
canDelete
canPublish

Forbidden patterns in frontend:

if (document.ownerId === user.id)
if (user.role === "admin")
if (document.status === "draft")

Security must always be enforced by the backend.